SIMPLE: lune
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lune
<hw>Lune</hw> <pr>(l⟦umac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>luna</ets> moon: cf. F. <ets>lune</ets>. See <er>Luna</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Anything in the shape of a half moon.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A figure in the form of a
crescent, bounded by two intersecting arcs of circles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A fit of lunacy or madness; a period of frenzy; a
crazy or unreasonable freak.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These dangerous, unsafe <qex>lunes</qex> i' the king.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lunet</ent>⟦br⟧
